snippet: Bertha, Seattle’s troubled tunnel machine, is on the move after being stalled for more than a year.
abstract: Washington State Transportation Dept announces that Bertha, giant boring device being used to dig tunnel in Seattle that is key element in Alaskan Way Viaduct Replacement Project, has been repaired and is working once again.
lead_paragraph: Bertha, Seattle’s troubled tunnel machine, is on the move after being stalled for more than a year.

headline.main: Washington: Giant Bore Is Digging Again
headline.print_headline: Washington: Giant Bore Is Digging Again
